Got it.

757
00:45:47.245 --> 00:45:48.913
Step one: I infiltrate the lab.

758
00:45:49.080 --> 00:45:51.207
Two: Find the head scientist's computer.

759
00:45:51.374 --> 00:45:54.694
Miles: That lady with the bike is the head
scientist. I saw her in this documentary.

760
00:45:54.835 --> 00:45:57.129
Peter: Cool! Step three:
I reexamine my personal biases.

761
00:45:57.296 --> 00:45:58.798
Step four: I hack the computer.

762
00:45:58.965 --> 00:46:00.341
It's not technically hacking.

763
00:46:00.508 --> 00:46:02.385
Not now. I just lost my train of thought.

764
00:46:02.551 --> 00:46:05.680
Step five: Download the important stuff.
I'll know it when I see it.

765
00:46:05.846 --> 00:46:08.933
Step six: I grab a bagel
from the cafeteria and run.

766
00:46:09.100 --> 00:46:10.559
Miles: So. what am I doing?

767
00:46:10.726 --> 00:46:13.938
Step seven: You stay here.
You're lookout. Very important.

768
00:46:14.105 --> 00:46:18.693
Look. man. You gotta teach me how to do
spider-man stuff or I won't be able to help.

769
00:46:19.318 --> 00:46:22.363
Watch and learn. kid! I'll quiz ya later!

770
00:46:24.991 --> 00:46:28.536
Why did I get stuck with the janky.
old. broke hobo spider-man?!

771
00:46:30.121 --> 00:46:31.247
That's new.

772
00:46:31.414 --> 00:46:32.456
[Car approaching]

773
00:46:37.753 --> 00:46:39.380
[III]

774
00:46:41.257 --> 00:46:42.258
Kingpin.

775
00:46:46.345 --> 00:46:49.390
What am I doing? What am I doing?
What am I doing? What am I doing?

776
00:47:06.449 --> 00:47:07.867
[Whispering] Peter!

777
00:47:08.034 --> 00:47:09.618
Peter!

778
00:47:10.286 --> 00:47:11.120
Ah! Peter!

779
00:47:11.287 --> 00:47:13.390
- [Whispering] What are you doing here?
- Kingpin's here.

780
00:47:13.414 --> 00:47:14.623
Just move over.

781
00:47:14.790 --> 00:47:17.543
You're steppin' on my foot.
Go back outside.

782
00:47:17.710 --> 00:47:21.047
No! I can't sit there and let spider-man
die without doing anything about it.

783
00:47:21.213 --> 00:47:23.299
I'm not doing that again.

784
00:47:24.050 --> 00:47:25.634
What?

785
00:47:25.801 --> 00:47:29.180
Most people I meet
in the workplace try to kill me...

786
00:47:29.764 --> 00:47:31.265
So you're a nice change of pace.

787
00:47:32.683 --> 00:47:34.852
Mr. Fisk! Look at this data.

788
00:47:35.019 --> 00:47:37.899
I know you can't really understand it.
but these are really good numbers.

789
00:47:38.856 --> 00:47:40.816
And I got the password.

790
00:47:40.983 --> 00:47:43.361
Mr. Fisk. If we fire again this week...

791
00:47:43.527 --> 00:47:45.905
There could be a black hole
under Brooklyn.

792
00:47:46.072 --> 00:47:47.573
You see this? And this?

793
00:47:47.740 --> 00:47:51.702
This is multiple dimensions beginning
to crash into each other.

794
00:47:51.869 --> 00:47:54.538
This is pretty standard
spider-man stakes. You get used to it.

795
00:47:54.705 --> 00:47:58.125
Watch this. He's gonna say.
"you've got 24 hours."

796
00:47:58.292 --> 00:47:59.418
You've got 24 hours.

797
00:47:59.585 --> 00:48:03.130
What this means is there could be
a rupture in the space-time continuum.

798
00:48:03.297 --> 00:48:06.759
Ooh. That's bad. Actually. everything
she said was bad. I was lying before.

799
00:48:08.844 --> 00:48:10.262
[III]

800
00:48:15.643 --> 00:48:18.479
Head scientist:
Hold on. Let me get you some more data.

801
00:48:20.231 --> 00:48:22.817
- What are you doing. bud?
- I can't move.

802
00:48:22.983 --> 00:48:27.488
Okay. relax your fingers. We don't
have time. Just let go. Be in the moment.

803
00:48:27.655 --> 00:48:29.532
I am in the moment.
It's a terrible moment.

804
00:48:29.698 --> 00:48:32.201
- I'm not refusing.
- No more excuses.

805
00:48:32.368 --> 00:48:33.786
I just need more time.

806
00:48:33.953 --> 00:48:35.633
They're right there.
They're gonna see you.

807
00:48:36.163 --> 00:48:37.790
Miles. you gotta unstick.

808
00:48:38.207 --> 00:48:39.708
What do you do to relax?

809
00:48:40.459 --> 00:48:43.045
Relax. Okay. okay. okay.

810
00:48:43.212 --> 00:48:45.589
I needless to say I. uh. uh I

811
00:48:46.590 --> 00:48:48.050
oh. for crying out loud.

812
00:48:48.426 --> 00:48:50.678
I calling it quits
now. baby. I'm a wreck I

813
00:48:51.137 --> 00:48:53.139
[humming]

814
00:48:53.639 --> 00:48:55.307
I ooh ii

815
00:48:58.352 --> 00:49:00.072
[in normal voice]
Teenagers: Just the worst.

816
00:49:02.815 --> 00:49:04.815
- Miles. where did you go?
- Miles: I'm right here.

817
00:49:04.859 --> 00:49:07.987
- Where? I can't see ya.
- I'm right in front of you.

818
00:49:08.154 --> 00:49:11.282
- Can spider-man turn invisible?
- Not in my universe.

819
00:49:11.449 --> 00:49:12.658
You just poked me in my eye!

820
00:49:12.825 --> 00:49:14.994
This is incredible.
Some kind of fight or flight thing.

821
00:49:15.161 --> 00:49:16.620
What's that?

822
00:49:18.956 --> 00:49:21.500
Remember this password.
D-g-f—a-m-p-e-s-a-n-d...

823
00:49:21.667 --> 00:49:22.501
Slow down!

824
00:49:22.668 --> 00:49:26.297
M4$sszsss454sss.

825
00:49:26.464 --> 00:49:28.400
- I need to write it down!
- Download the schematic.

826
00:49:28.424 --> 00:49:30.551
- How do I do that?
- While I turn on the charm.

827
00:49:32.970 --> 00:49:34.013
Spider-man?

828
00:49:34.180 --> 00:49:36.724
- Oh. hey. Didn't see you there.
- Wow!

829
00:49:37.850 --> 00:49:42.021
Okay. I'm kinda freaking out right now.
You're supposed to be dead.

830
00:49:42.188 --> 00:49:45.399
Surprise! Okay. That's a no-no.
We don't like that.

831
00:49:45.566 --> 00:49:46.692
This is fascinating.

832
00:49:47.276 --> 00:49:48.819
Okay. that's my face.

833
00:49:48.986 --> 00:49:51.113
An entirely different Peter Parker.

834
00:49:51.280 --> 00:49:53.782
Little bit of a gut.
perhaps from dimensional warping.

835
00:49:53.949 --> 00:49:56.577
Oh. yeah-yeah-yeah.
I was way flatter before I warped.

836
00:49:56.744 --> 00:49:59.538
Travel through the multiverse appears
to have deteriorated the...

837
00:50:00.581 --> 00:50:02.458
Miles: What was the rest?!

838
00:50:04.084 --> 00:50:08.005
Hey. how old are you?
'Cause you don't look a day over 35.

839
00:50:08.756 --> 00:50:10.901
Head scientist: They said
I was crazy! They said I was crazy!

840
00:50:10.925 --> 00:50:12.445
Peter:
You showed 'em you're not crazy.

841
00:50:12.718 --> 00:50:14.261
This might pinch a little.

842
00:50:16.263 --> 00:50:18.807
- Ow! Ow!
- I know. I just need to get these samples.

843
00:50:18.974 --> 00:50:19.808
Okay.

844
00:50:19.975 --> 00:50:21.727
Miles:
Organize your desktop. lady.

845
00:50:22.311 --> 00:50:25.356
Wow. Just complete cellular decay.

846
00:50:26.649 --> 00:50:29.461
- I've never seen anything like this.
- [Whispering] What are you doing?

847
00:50:29.485 --> 00:50:31.487
Miles:
I'm just taking the whole thing.

848
00:50:31.654 --> 00:50:33.197
And obviously you've been glitching.

849
00:50:33.364 --> 00:50:36.367
[In normal voice] "Glitchin'"? No.
Why would you even say that?

850
00:50:36.534 --> 00:50:39.495
If you stay in this dimension too long.
your body's gonna disintegrate.

851
00:50:39.662 --> 00:50:41.872
Do you know how painful
that would be. Peter Parker?

852
00:50:42.039 --> 00:50:42.873
I don't know.

853
00:50:43.040 --> 00:50:45.000
You can't imagine.

854
00:50:45.167 --> 00:50:47.044
And I. for one...

855
00:50:47.211 --> 00:50:48.879
Can't wait to watch.

856
00:50:51.090 --> 00:50:52.330
What did you say your name was?

857
00:50:52.383 --> 00:50:54.510
Dr. Olivia octavius.

858
00:50:55.344 --> 00:50:57.221
[III]

859
00:51:02.059 --> 00:51:04.853
Can I assume
that your friends call you doc ock?

860
00:51:05.020 --> 00:51:07.147
My friends actually call me Liv.

861
00:51:07.314 --> 00:51:09.692
My enemies call me doc ock.

862
00:51:09.858 --> 00:51:11.151
I got this! Run!

863
00:51:11.318 --> 00:51:13.195
Doc ock: Who are you talking to?

864
00:51:15.531 --> 00:51:18.033
Peter: I got it!
Doc ock: Oh. you "got it." Peter?

865
00:51:20.244 --> 00:51:21.704
Peter: I got it handled. buddy!

866
00:51:23.622 --> 00:51:25.082
Everything is fine!

867
00:51:27.585 --> 00:51:31.171
- Okay. this is a little bit bad.
- Doc ock: You're chatty.

868
00:51:31.338 --> 00:51:32.418
[In normal voice] Gotta go.

869
00:51:35.050 --> 00:51:37.636
This is the moment
that I'm iosin' the fight.

870
00:51:39.763 --> 00:51:42.433
Let me tell you the good news.
We don't need the monitor.

871
00:51:42.600 --> 00:51:44.310
-Oh! Doc ock: Peter!

872
00:51:45.185 --> 00:51:48.856
You didn't tell me
you had an invisible friend!

873
00:51:49.023 --> 00:51:50.691
Could you give me that back.
young man?

874
00:51:50.858 --> 00:51:52.401
Miles: Peter!

875
00:51:52.568 --> 00:51:55.321
It's proprietary.

876
00:51:59.783 --> 00:52:00.868
Peter: Oh!

877
00:52:01.702 --> 00:52:04.246
- This'd be a good time to turn invisible.
- Yep.

878
00:52:04.413 --> 00:52:07.124
Okay. not gonna turn invisible.
Selecting a bagel.

879
00:52:07.666 --> 00:52:09.126
Act super normal.

880
00:52:09.293 --> 00:52:10.294
Spider-man?

881
00:52:10.461 --> 00:52:13.172
- You know. that's funny. I get that a lot.
- Hey.

882
00:52:13.339 --> 00:52:15.466
- Spider-man?
- Hey! Hands up!

883
00:52:15.633 --> 00:52:16.967
Now we do a switchy—switchy.

884
00:52:17.134 --> 00:52:19.261
Woman: Get back here!
Where do you think you're going?

885
00:52:19.428 --> 00:52:20.428
He took a bagel!

886
00:52:20.471 --> 00:52:23.682
- Time to swing. just like I taught ya.
- When did you teach me that?

887
00:52:23.849 --> 00:52:26.352
I didn't. It's a little
joke for team-building.

888
00:52:28.228 --> 00:52:31.690
- All right. you ready?
- Of course I'm not ready! Oh! Oh. oh!

889
00:52:32.441 --> 00:52:33.484
I can't do this yet!

890
00:52:33.651 --> 00:52:35.653
Everybody knows
that the best way to learn...

891
00:52:35.819 --> 00:52:37.821
Is under intense
life-threatening pressure.

892
00:52:41.075 --> 00:52:42.951
Come on. come on. come on.

893
00:52:49.166 --> 00:52:51.251
[III]

894
00:52:53.712 --> 00:52:55.547
Peter:
What are you doing down there?

895
00:52:55.714 --> 00:52:57.424
I run better than I swing.

896
00:52:57.591 --> 00:53:00.552
You gotta swing or they'll catch you.

897
00:53:00.719 --> 00:53:03.055
This is what you wanted.

898
00:53:14.692 --> 00:53:15.693
[Gasps]

899
00:53:15.859 --> 00:53:17.319
Come back. little boy.

900
00:53:17.486 --> 00:53:19.780
Aim with your hips!
Look where you want it to hit.

901
00:53:19.947 --> 00:53:22.157
Square your shoulders.
Don't forget to follow through!

902
00:53:22.324 --> 00:53:23.659
Don't shoot off your back foot.

903
00:53:23.826 --> 00:53:26.370
- That's too many things!
- Then stop listening to me!

904
00:53:26.537 --> 00:53:29.707
That's the best idea you've had all day!

905
00:53:36.714 --> 00:53:39.133
Nice. miles!

906
00:53:42.469 --> 00:53:44.138
- Ha. ha!
- Good. You're doin' it.

907
00:53:44.304 --> 00:53:46.890
Double tap to release
and thwip it out again.

908
00:53:47.057 --> 00:53:48.726
Thwip and release.

909
00:53:48.892 --> 00:53:52.020
- And thwip. Release. Thwip.
- Miles: And release.

910
00:53:52.187 --> 00:53:53.747
Peter:
You're a natural. Thwip. Release.

911
00:53:53.897 --> 00:53:56.400
- Feel the rhythm?
- Whoo-hoo! Thwip. And release!

912
00:53:56.567 --> 00:53:59.778
- Good. miles.
- I gotta say. you're amazing. man.

913
00:53:59.945 --> 00:54:01.321
We're a little team!

914
00:54:01.488 --> 00:54:03.157
Me as the teacher who could still do it.

915
00:54:03.323 --> 00:54:06.201
You as the student who can do it.
just not as good.

916
00:54:06.368 --> 00:54:09.163
I'm proud of us. Is there something
you want to say to me?

917
00:54:11.331 --> 00:54:12.374
Peter!

918
00:54:24.803 --> 00:54:26.346
- What the...?
- Peter: Who did that?

919
00:54:43.280 --> 00:54:44.448
[Doc ock grunts]

920
00:54:53.207 --> 00:54:54.249
Hey. guys.

921
00:54:54.416 --> 00:54:55.417
Gwanda?

922
00:54:55.584 --> 00:54:57.169
It's Gwen. actually.

923
00:54:57.336 --> 00:55:00.130
Oh. you know her. Very cool.

924
00:55:00.297 --> 00:55:02.090
I'm from another dimension.

925
00:55:02.257 --> 00:55:05.135
I mean. another-another dimension.

926
00:55:05.302 --> 00:55:07.982
Gwen: All right. people. Let's start
at the beginning one last time.

927
00:55:08.138 --> 00:55:12.434
My name is Gwen Stacy.
I was bitten by a radioactive spider.

928
00:55:12.601 --> 00:55:17.606
And for the last two years. I've been
the one and only spider-woman.

929
00:55:17.773 --> 00:55:19.441
You guys know the rest.

930
00:55:19.608 --> 00:55:21.109
I joined a band.

931
00:55:22.736 --> 00:55:24.696
Saved my dad.

932
00:55:27.407 --> 00:55:30.160
I couldn't save my best friend...

933
00:55:30.327 --> 00:55:31.995
Peter Parker...

934
00:55:33.539 --> 00:55:35.624
So now I save everyone else.

935
00:55:35.791 --> 00:55:38.544
And I don't do friends anymore...

936
00:55:38.710 --> 00:55:40.587
Just to avoid any distractions.

937
00:55:41.713 --> 00:55:45.717
And one day this weird thing happened.

938
00:55:46.134 --> 00:55:49.304
And I mean. like. really weird.

939
00:55:54.726 --> 00:55:57.396
I was blown into last week.

940
00:56:00.941 --> 00:56:02.818
Literally.

941
00:56:02.985 --> 00:56:06.321
I landed in New York.
but not my New York.

942
00:56:07.948 --> 00:56:10.909
Woman [on screen]: Lucky for these
folks. spider-man saved the day.

943
00:56:11.827 --> 00:56:14.872
Gwen: My spider-sense told me
to head to visions academy.

944
00:56:15.038 --> 00:56:16.164
You guys are early.

945
00:56:17.040 --> 00:56:19.877
Wasn't sure why until I met you.

946
00:56:21.962 --> 00:56:23.130
I like your haircut.

947
00:56:23.297 --> 00:56:25.007
You don't get to like my haircut.

948
00:56:25.173 --> 00:56:26.008
Let's go.

949
00:56:26.174 --> 00:56:27.654
How many more spider-people
are there?

950
00:56:27.801 --> 00:56:29.011
Save it for comic-con.

951
00:56:29.177 --> 00:56:30.387
What's comic-con?

952
00:56:32.973 --> 00:56:37.895
[Pen clicking]

953
00:56:39.813 --> 00:56:41.815
[III]

954
00:56:47.988 --> 00:56:49.448
Kingpin:
You're dead. spider-man.

955
00:56:49.615 --> 00:56:51.825
Wilson! What are you doing?

956
00:56:51.992 --> 00:56:53.035
Vanessa.

957
00:56:53.201 --> 00:56:54.328
Vanessa: Richard. come on.

958
00:56:58.123 --> 00:56:59.791
Vanessa! Richard!

959
00:57:01.376 --> 00:57:04.004
Don't look back. honey.
It's okay. It's okay.

960
00:57:04.171 --> 00:57:05.589
[Horn honking]

961
00:57:08.342 --> 00:57:09.676
[III]

962
00:57:18.352 --> 00:57:19.519
[Grunts]

963
00:57:22.981 --> 00:57:24.733
I killed spider-man.

964
00:57:25.275 --> 00:57:26.818
Why did I just see two more?

965
00:57:27.319 --> 00:57:29.154
There's three. actually.

966
00:57:29.696 --> 00:57:31.865
No. this is good. This is very. very good.

967
00:57:32.032 --> 00:57:33.867
This means you get what you want.

968
00:57:34.034 --> 00:57:36.536
It means my collider works.

969
00:57:37.245 --> 00:57:40.415
All we have to do is kill
a couple of spiders.

970
00:57:40.582 --> 00:57:42.751
And the collider will bring
your family back.

971
00:57:43.418 --> 00:57:45.837
As many families as you want.

972
00:57:54.888 --> 00:57:57.182
Tomorrow. at my collider.

973
00:57:57.849 --> 00:58:00.227
Our collider.

974
00:58:03.397 --> 00:58:04.481
He broke this?

975
00:58:04.648 --> 00:58:09.236
Yeah. He's actually really embarrassed
about it. so just keep it between us. okay?

976
00:58:09.403 --> 00:58:10.696
[Chuckles]

977
00:58:10.862 --> 00:58:14.533
I know where we can make a new one.
And we won't let him break it this time.

978
00:58:17.536 --> 00:58:18.912
I'm sorry about your friend.

979
00:58:20.622 --> 00:58:21.665
Thanks. miles.

980
00:58:24.167 --> 00:58:28.380
I know how hard this is. To have
to figure this stuff out on your own.

981
00:58:28.547 --> 00:58:31.550
It's kinda nice not being
the only spider-person around.

982
00:58:34.553 --> 00:58:38.640
If you ever decide to do friends again.
I could always open up a slot.

983
00:58:40.183 --> 00:58:42.728
I'll keep you posted.

984
00:58:43.353 --> 00:58:45.063
Miles: Cool.

985
00:58:46.940 --> 00:58:47.941
[Doorbell rings]

986
00:58:49.693 --> 00:58:51.361
We should probably go.

987
00:58:51.528 --> 00:58:54.322
Peter. we're literally on the doorstep.

988
00:58:54.489 --> 00:58:57.075
Peter: Bad idea. This is a bad idea.
Gwen: Just relax.

989
00:58:57.242 --> 00:59:01.580
May: You guys are all very sweet.
but no more fans today. please.

990
00:59:05.000 --> 00:59:06.376
I'm not ready for this.

991
00:59:07.878 --> 00:59:09.921
[III]

992
00:59:11.423 --> 00:59:12.966
Peter?

993
00:59:14.718 --> 00:59:16.553
Hey. aunt may.

994
00:59:16.720 --> 00:59:21.183
So this is gonna sound crazy.
but I'm pretty sure that I'm from an...

995
00:59:21.349 --> 00:59:22.768
An alternate dimension.

996
00:59:25.854 --> 00:59:27.773
You look tired. Peter.

997
00:59:27.939 --> 00:59:30.025
Well. I am tired.

998
00:59:30.192 --> 00:59:33.236
- And older. And thicker.
- Yeah. I've heard that already.

999
00:59:33.403 --> 00:59:35.655
Oh. jeez. Are those sweatpants?

1000
00:59:35.822 --> 00:59:37.949
Yup. that's what they are.

1001
00:59:38.116 --> 00:59:39.785
I was there...

